  "text": "Regulatory bodies like the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) are major constituencies linked to environmental issues. These agencies establish regulations and control enforcement mechanisms such as penalties, fines and the ability to pursue legal prosecution of violators. They also establish voluntary programs which seek corporate commitment to actions that improve the natural environment (see [CITATION_1] for a recent meta-analysis on the issue).",
